<dl id="n08043a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08043a">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08043a"> 43(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> following which he silently left <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n08043a"><li>FW 471.27 </li><li><a href="../../flex/qC/lexqC.htm#n08043a">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/qC/l39qC.htm#n08043a">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n08043a">MS BL 47482b-17v</ms> </li><li>JJA 57:036 <a name="qA1d" href="../../FF/fdra/qda.htm#qC1d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/q/qC1d.htm#n08043a">Draft: III&sect;2C.1</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Report of Cloonfallegh (Kiltimagh) shooting]</font>: <font color="green">[A farmer was shot and police, suspecting a neighbour, eavesdropped and collected evidence to bring him to trial.]</font> Sergeant Feely &hellip; pulling off his boots &hellip; noiselessly slipped down the kitchen chimney &hellip; Remaining there for an hour, he overheard a conversation, <mark>following which he silently left</mark>. &hellip; The prisoner&apos;s son &hellip; deposed: &hellip; He took off his clothes and shoes and said something about Thomas Carney, that he had shot him &hellip; I saw a gun with my father &hellip; He had it since the hay-time. <small> <a name="II2jan24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#II2jan24"><cite title="source">Irish Independent</cite></a> (2 January 1924) 5/1</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
